
Textual representation of the "Does the string have an unterminated
comment (\*) in it" DFA. The DFA "accepts" a given sequence of
characters if it contains no unterminated comments. The DFA
"rejects" a given sequence of characters if the sequence contains an
unterminated comment.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

NORMAL (accept) <-- the start state
      /: SLASH
      ": IN_STRING
      ': IN_CHAR
      \n: START (Action: print new line)
      other: START (Action: print char)

SLASH (/) (accept)
      *: IN_COMMENT (Action, print space)
      /: SLASH (Action: print /)
      ": IN_STRING (Action: print /, then ")
      ': IN_CHAR (Action: print /, then ')
      \n: START (Action: print /, then new line)
      other: START (Action: print /, then char)

IN_COMMENT (/*) (reject)
      *: COMMENT_STAR
      \n: IN_COMMENT (Action: print new line)
      other: IN_COMMENT

COMMENT_STAR (/*...*) (reject)
      /: START
      *: COMMENT_STAR
      \n: IN_COMMENT (Action: print new line)
      other: IN_COMMENT

IN_STRING (accept)
      ":  NORMAL (Action: print ")
      \:  STRING_ESC
      \n: IN_STRING (Action: print new line)
      other: IN_STRING (Action: print char)
      
STRING_ESC (accept)
      any: IN_STRING (Action: print \ and char)

IN_CHAR (accept)
      ':  NORMAL (Action: print ')
      \:  CHAR_ESC
      \n: IN_CHAR (Action: print new line)
      other: IN_CHAR (Action: print char)

CHAR_ESC (accept)
      any: IN_CHAR (Action: print \ and char)

